1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT TO PROVIDE THAT THE DEPARTMENT OF TRANSPORTATION IS NOT
3 REQUIRED TO SERVE OR JOIN SPOUSES OF PROPERTY OWNERS IN
4 CONDEMNATION ACTIONS AND TO MAKE TECHNICAL CHANGES.
5 The General Assembly of North Carolina enacts:
6 SECTION 1. G.S. 136-103 reads as rewritten:
7 "§ 136-103. Institution of action and deposit.
8 (a) In case condemnation shall become necessary becomes necessary, the Department of
9 Transportation shall institute a civil action by filing in the superior court of any county in which
10 the land is located a complaint and a declaration of taking declaring that such land, easement, or
11 interest therein the land or an easement or interest in the land is thereby taken for the use of the
12 Department of Transportation.Department. The Department is not required to serve or join a
13 person whose only interest in the land is the possibility of a future election under G.S. 29-30.
14 (b) Said The declaration shall contain or have attached thereto to it the following:
15 (1) A statement of the authority under which and the public use for which said the
16 land is taken.
17 (2) A description of the entire tract or tracts affected by said the taking sufficient
18 for the identification thereof.of it.
