31 SECTION 2. G.S. 29-30 reads as rewritten:
32 "§ 29-30. Election of surviving spouse to take life interest in lieu of intestate share provided.
33 (a) Except as provided in this subsection, in lieu of the intestate share provided in
34 G.S. 29-14 or G.S. 29-21, or of the elective share provided in G.S. 30-3.1, the surviving spouse
35 of an intestate or the surviving spouse who has petitioned for an elective share is entitled to take
36 as the surviving spouse's intestate share or elective share a life estate in one third in value of all
37 the real estate of which the deceased spouse was seised and possessed of an estate of inheritance
38 at any time during coverture. the marriage. The surviving spouse is not entitled to take a life
39 estate in any of the following circumstances:
40 …
41 (3c) Any real estate taken by the Department of Transportation in a condemnation
42 action initiated before the deceased spouse's death.
43 …."
44 SECTION 3. This act becomes effective October 1, 2025, and applies to
45 condemnation actions initiated on or after that date.
